  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we start having, you know, coupons for everything and then that's how our lives started changing a little bit.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they start the black market.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then little by little, you know, as I told you before, the Jewish population in Rhodes Island, they were not very rich, and they were just-- just receiving to-- like aid from their own children that were in America, in Africa, and everything.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when the war start, then they didn't send it anymore because the posts were not coming anymore, and they were just starting to feel like starvation and all this.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They couldn't buy, especially with those black market price.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that's when the Jewish population in Rhodes Island started, you know, to feel uncomfortable.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Were there any Nazi or fascist groups in your town that-- that you lived?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Were there what?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were fascists, but we all belong.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Myself, I was a small Italian [INAUDIBLE] so was all the Jewish-- were all the Jewish girl, the Jewish boy because it was like fun.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was like going every Sunday, to, you know, like you go to seminar.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were going there to sing songs and everything, and it was fun to be with the other one, with the Italian girls, Italian boys, and it was like nothing.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was-- we did-- because actually, we like Italy, up to then, you know, we were treated like every other Italian, Jews or non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "At the beginning, you know, Mussolini was very much lenient towards the-- the-- the Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, even in Italy, he was-- they use to call him that he was a friend of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
